{"key":"post-9412441","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>9412441</id>\n<content>After the mist evaporates, mist again about 2 hours later.&amp;nbsp; This wetting of the substrate, and then drying, is a major pinning trigger.&amp;nbsp; It's not as big as lots of fresh air exchange, but it's more important than maintaining a constant 99% humidity.&amp;nbsp; You can get a decent mechanical hygrometer for under $20.&amp;nbsp; Google &lt;i&gt;mechanical hygrometer&lt;/i&gt;.&amp;nbsp; Disregard all the threads you find saying digitals are better.&amp;nbsp; They're not using them in near-saturation humidity.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>9412449</next>\n<prev>9411816</prev>\n<first>9411545</first>\n<last>9413204</last>\n<when>1229022904</when>\n<utime>12/11/08 09:15 PM</utime>\n</post>"}